CNCP v1 23589
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#13886: In some cases, the return type of useTemplateRef is inferred as any",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:16:01.370945+00:00",
  "text": "In some cases, the return type of useTemplateRef is inferred as any\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.5.21\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```vue\n<script setup lang=\"ts\">\nimport { useTemplateRef , computed} from 'vue'\nimport DisplayN from './DisplayN.vue'\n\n// The type of this variable is inferred as any\nconst compRef = useTemplateRef('compRef')\nconst delta = 1\nconst n = computed(() => compRef.value?.getN())\n</script>\n\n<template>\n  <DisplayN ref=\"compRef\" :delta=\"delta\" />\n  <input v-model=\"n\"/>\n</template>\n```\nSee Demo for details\n\n### What is expected?\n\nAutomatically infer the type of `compRef`\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\n`compRef` is inferred as any.\n\n### System Info\n\n```shell\n\n```\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\nIf you remove`v-model=\"n\"` or `:delta=\"delta\"`, the type of `compRef` can be inferred correctly.🫠",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: types",
    "language-tools"
  ],
